  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> black rice</strong> to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and cook over a high heat for 30 min or until it's tender (it will still have a slight bite to it when cooked)</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and set aside</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/nourishing-curried-haddock-and-black-rice-bowl/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and grate the<strong> carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>grated carrot</strong> to a bowl with the<strong> nigella seeds</strong> and mix to combine &ndash; this is your <strong>carrot salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/nourishing-curried-haddock-and-black-rice-bowl/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dice the <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> and<strong> cucumber</strong> finely</p>\r\n<p>Strip the <strong>mint</strong> <strong>leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them finely (save some leaves for garnish!)</p>\r\n<p>Chop the<strong> coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/nourishing-curried-haddock-and-black-rice-bowl/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>tomato</strong>, <strong>cucumber</strong> and <strong>chopped herbs</strong> in a small bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; this is your <strong>kachumber</strong>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/nourishing-curried-haddock-and-black-rice-bowl/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Line a baking tray with&nbsp;<strong>tin foil</strong>&nbsp;and add the<strong>&nbsp;curry powder</strong></p>\r\n<p>Pat the&nbsp;<strong>haddock bites&nbsp;</strong>dry with&nbsp;kitchen paper&nbsp;and add them to the tray&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Turn the<strong>&nbsp;haddock bites</strong>&nbsp;several times into the curry powder until they're fully coated</p>\r\n<p>Lightly drizzle them with&nbsp;<strong>olive oil</strong>&nbsp;and put the tray in the oven for 5 min or until cooked through</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/nourishing-curried-haddock-and-black-rice-bowl/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong>&nbsp;garlic&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine the&nbsp;<strong>chopped garlic</strong>&nbsp;(Don't like raw garlic? Go easy!)&nbsp;with the juice of 1/2&nbsp;<span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span><strong>&nbsp;lemon</strong>&nbsp;and 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\">&nbsp;[2 tbsp]&nbsp;</span><strong>olive oil&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Season with a pinch of&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>pepper </strong>&ndash;&nbsp;this is your&nbsp;<strong>lemony dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/nourishing-curried-haddock-and-black-rice-bowl/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the remaining <strong>lemon</strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/nourishing-curried-haddock-and-black-rice-bowl/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>kachumber</strong>, <strong>carrot salad</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>spinach leaves&nbsp;</strong>over the<span class=\"text-highlight\"> <strong>black rice</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>Top with the<strong> curried haddock bites</strong>, garnish with a wedge of <strong>lemon</strong> and the <strong>mint leaves</strong></p>\r\n<p>Drizzle over the <strong>lemony dressing </strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
